#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:2
msgid ""
"NXP i.MX 8M Plus and i.MX 8M Mini Evaluation Kits (``imx8mp-evk``, ``imx8mm-"
"evk``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:4
msgid ""
"The ``imx8mp-evk`` and ``imx8mm-evk`` machine models the i.MX 8M Plus and i."
"MX 8M Mini Evaluation Kits, based on i.MX 8M Plus and i.MX8M Mini SoCs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:9
msgid "Supported devices"
msgstr "支援的裝置"

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:11
msgid ""
"The ``imx8mp-evk`` and ``imx8mm-evk`` machines implement the following "
"devices:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:14
msgid "Up to 4 Cortex-A53 cores"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:15
msgid "Generic Interrupt Controller (GICv3)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:16
msgid "4 UARTs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:17
msgid "3 USDHC Storage Controllers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:18
msgid "1 Designware PCI Express Controller"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:19
msgid "1 Ethernet Controller"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:20
msgid "2 Designware USB 3 Controllers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:21
msgid "5 GPIO Controllers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:22
msgid "6 I2C Controllers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:23
msgid "3 SPI Controllers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:24
msgid "3 Watchdogs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:25
msgid "6 General Purpose Timers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:26
msgid "Secure Non-Volatile Storage (SNVS) including an RTC"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:27
msgid "Clock Tree"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:30
msgid "Boot options"
msgstr "開機選項"

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:32
msgid ""
"The ``imx8mp-evk`` and ``imx8mm-evk`` machines can start a Linux kernel "
"directly using the standard ``-kernel`` functionality."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:36
msgid "Direct Linux Kernel Boot"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:38
msgid ""
"Probably the easiest way to get started with a whole Linux system on the "
"machine is to generate an image with Buildroot. Version 2024.11.1 is tested "
"at the time of writing and involves two steps. First run the following "
"commands in the toplevel directory of the Buildroot source tree:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:43 ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:66
msgid "For i.MX 8M Plus EVK:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:45
msgid ""
"$ make freescale_imx8mpevk_defconfig\n"
"$ make"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:50 ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:77
msgid "For i.MX 8M Mini EVK:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:52
msgid ""
"$ make freescale_imx8mmevk_defconfig\n"
"$ make"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:57
msgid ""
"Once finished successfully there is an ``output/image`` subfolder. Navigate "
"into it and resize the SD card image to a power of two:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:60
msgid "$ qemu-img resize sdcard.img 256M"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:64
msgid "Now that everything is prepared the machine can be started as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:68
msgid ""
"$ qemu-system-aarch64 -M imx8mp-evk \\\n"
"    -display none -serial null -serial stdio \\\n"
"    -kernel Image \\\n"
"    -dtb imx8mp-evk.dtb \\\n"
"    -append \"root=/dev/mmcblk2p2\" \\\n"
"    -drive file=sdcard.img,if=sd,bus=2,format=raw,id=mmcblk2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:79
msgid ""
"$ qemu-system-aarch64 -M imx8mm-evk -smp 4 -m 2G \\\n"
"    -display none -serial null -serial stdio \\\n"
"    -kernel Image \\\n"
"    -dtb imx8mm-evk.dtb \\\n"
"    -append \"root=/dev/mmcblk2p2\" \\\n"
"    -drive file=sdcard.img,if=sd,bus=2,format=raw,id=mmcblk2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:89
msgid "KVM Acceleration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:91
msgid ""
"To enable hardware-assisted acceleration via KVM, append ``-accel kvm`` to "
"the command line. While this speeds up performance significantly, be aware "
"of the following limitations:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:95
msgid ""
"The ``imx8mp-evk`` and ``imx8mm-evk`` machines are not included under the "
"\"virtualization use case\" of :doc:`QEMU's security policy </system/"
"security>`.  This means that you should not trust that it can contain "
"malicious guests, whether it is run using TCG or KVM. If you don't trust "
"your guests and you're relying on QEMU to be the security boundary, you want "
"to choose another machine such as ``virt``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:102
msgid ""
"Rather than Cortex-A53 CPUs, the same CPU type as the host's will be used. "
"This is a limitation of KVM and may not work with guests with a tight "
"dependency on Cortex-A53."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/imx8m.rst:105
msgid ""
"No EL2 and EL3 exception levels are available which is also a KVM "
"limitation. Direct kernel boot should work but running U-Boot, TF-A, etc. "
"won't succeed."
msgstr ""
